title: Live updates: Deadly Tropical Storm Hilary makes landfall in Mexico
description: Tropical Storm Hilary heads toward Southern California, where heavy rainfall, winds and flooding are expected. Follow live updates as we cover the storm.

title: Conditions deteriorating in Southern California, with flood alerts, high winds
Ecuador votes for president just days after candidate’s assassination
description: Some Ecuadoran officials worry that the violence could escalate in the days ahead or even as voters head to the polls Sunday.

title: Anti-corruption candidate seeks upset win in Guatemala presidential vote
description: The big question Sunday wasn’t just whether Bernardo Arévalos could win the Guatemala presidential race. It’s whether a political establishment long criticized as corrupt would let him govern.

title: IMF chief cites her life behind Iron Curtain in warning of new Cold War
description: Kristalina Georgieva grew up on the wrong side of the line dividing two superpowers. The IMF chief fears a new era of rival blocs could lead the world to repeat the errors of the Cold War.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Russia-Ukraine war news: Zelensky vows response after Chernihiv strike kills 7
description: The attack on a theater in Chernihiv, some 80 miles north of Kyiv, left at least 7 dead and injured more than 140 people.

title: Taliban bringing water to Afghanistan’s parched plains via massive canal
description: Two years after taking power, the Taliban is overseeing its first major infrastructure project: A 115-mile canal that will divert water from the Amu Darya river.

title: Ukraine running out of options to retake significant territory
description: Ukraine’s inability to demonstrate decisive success on the battlefield is stoking fears that the conflict is becoming a stalemate and international support could erode.
